WRITING.TEXT: it is draining doing readings. Though I noticed as I did more readings regularly. I sort of adjusted it little by little. like getting use to going for a run, you get use to running more over time. though after I've done a few I still get drained. I can't do readings if I'm personally stressed or feeling sick etc. just pace yourself and take rests. you need some none reading time too to relax/unwind/have fun. Sometimes you can feel a bit bad about not doing readings when people ask, but you can't give a good reading if your tired or stressed etc. So know when you need a break and don't feel bad if you need a break. I started putting healthy boundaries for free readings. since doing them all the time was too draining and I never really got a break otherwise. I needed time for myself to relax etc. so I set out a time each week to do free readings. which helped for me. but you could always try free reading slots too. What ever you feel allows you time to relax and recharge.
